<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend/Search/Lucene/Documents/Docx.php, OpenXml.php, Pptx.php and Xlsx.php all have a line like this:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code> 
if (class_exists ( 'ZipArchive' )) {
</code></pre>

<p>On systems where the Zip extension is not loaded, this generates the warning:</p>

<p>Warning: Zend_Loader::include_once(ZipArchive.php) [zend-loader.include-once]: failed to open stream: No such file or directory in /Users/rob/ZFiA/code/lib/Zend/Loader.php on line 89</p>

<p>Fix is to change the class_exists() call to:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code> 
if (class_exists ( 'ZipArchive' , false)) {
</code></pre>

